<subSubSection id="4055FF015F1624D3F66581273C5DA37B" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="notes">
<paragraph id="7ECEF7FCAD7829DC3133532632DA0FAF" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D416EC27D901FBB15B728981A03BD48C" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
First report for South Africa and sub-Saharan Africa. 
<taxonomicName id="177CB8F67C69C7E46E2EB9463443DB5B" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa infirma" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="infirma">
<emphasis id="CAC9FD0A3B33FE587AF8FEF311531721" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Poa infirma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the diploid parents of the tetraploid species, 
<taxonomicName id="55982CC28831325EF548927F6E7B7002" authorityName="L. Sp. Pl. 1: 68" authorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa annua" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="annua">
<emphasis id="06C3650E77BED5985316220299879283" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Poa annua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species is self-compatible, inbreeding. 2 
<emphasis id="F8E849F34671ED960CC5321CB5F2752C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="2F85919E00BE117943EDD5BCEE24EA49" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">14</emphasis>
. - 
<emphasis id="4A68256A0CCFDAF905931F6E2E490CC0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Mimi</emphasis>
genotype.
</paragraph>
